<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Orel Oblast Soviet Abolished; Duma To Be Elected </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1201152994 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 12 Jan 94 
First Edition p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM1201152994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Nikolay Kireyev report from the "Yesterday, Today, </F>
Tomorrow" roundup: "Oblast Duma To Replace Soviet"] 
  [Text] An Oblast Duma will take the place of the Oblast 
Soviet of People's Deputies in Smolensk. 
  Administration Chief Anatoliy Glushenkov signed a decree on 
the representative (legislative) organ of state power, and 
provisional statutes on the Duma and the election of deputies 
have been ratified. 
  At its sitting the Orel Oblast Soviet of People's Deputies 
session examined the questions of reforming the representative 
organs of power and local self-government. 
  Statutes were ratified concerning the Oblast Duma, local 
self-government for the transitional period, and elections to 
these organs of power. They are scheduled for 20 March 1994. 

</TEXT>

