<DATE1>  13 Jan 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gaydar Resignation Hint Viewed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1201155594 Moscow KOMSOMOLSKAYA PRAVDA in Russian 12 Jan 
94 p 2 </F>

<F P=103> PM1201155594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KOMSOMOLSKAYA PRAVDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Sergey Razin: "Will Gaydar Resign?"] </F>
  [Text] The president has again issued an edict to 
reorganize the government. A large number of officials of 
various kinds have been laid off right up to the level of vice 
premiers -- their number has declined from nine to four. And 
only two of them will be first deputy heads of the cabinet. 
Only 20 ministries, 24 state committees, and 20 departments 
are left. 
  At first glance these figures confirm the official story of 
the latest government reshuffle: The inflated apparatus must be 
dealt with. But behind this reduction one can discern a 
tactical gain for the agrarian and industrial lobbyists and 
their leaders at the helm of power. 
  Premier Chernomyrdin has been given a week to personally 
appoint his deputies and ministers. Already observers are 
united in the opinion that it will be suggested that O. 
Soskovets and Ye. Gaydar become the first vice premiers and A. 
Zaveryukha and Yu. Yarov mere vice premiers. Of course this 
layout could be different. If only because at a recent press 
conference Gaydar dropped a transparent hint that he might not 
join the government. It is true that he did not say everything 
about his doubts. But the absence of his comrades in arms A. 
Chubays and B. Fedorov on the list of vice premiers needs no 
special comment. If the reformers' key figures are deprived of 
their powers then Gaydar will yet again be in the unenviable 
role of "whipping boy." 
  With this selection of vice premiers inflation will go 
sky-high by the spring and the future of privatization will look 
vague to say the least. With this disposition of forces Gaydar 
and "Russia's Choice" will most likely join the hidden 
[glukhaya] opposition. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

