<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Retains Chubays as Deputy Prime Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301123694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1136 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1301123694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 13 tass -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin has decreed that Anatoliy Chubays, chairman of the 
Russian State Property Managing Committee, will hold his post of 
a deputy prime minister in the new cabinet, the press service of 
the Russian president reported on Thursday. 
  Chubays was appointed deputy chairman of the government 
above 
the number of four vice-premiers named in Yeltsin's decree of 
January 10, the press service said. 

</TEXT>

