<H3> <TI>   Decree Issued on Helping Print Media Over Problems </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1201170594 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 13 Jan 94 
First Edition p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM1201170594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Russian Federation Government Decree No. 15, signed by </F>
Chernomyrdin and dated 10 January 1994: "Questions of Ensuring 
Publication and Dissemination of the Mass Media and Printed 
Matter"] 
  [Text] The Russian Federation Government decrees that: 
  1. Russian Federation Council of Ministers-Government Decree 
No. 1233 "On the Revaluation of the Fixed Capital (Funds) of 
Enterprises and Organizations" of 25 November 1993 regarding the 
revaluation of the fixed capital of printing enterprises, 
including those forming part of publishing and printing 
complexes, shall be suspended for three months. 
  The Russian Federation Finance Ministry and the Russian 
Federation Economics Ministry in conjunction with the Russian 
Federation Committee for the Press shall elaborate within this 
period a mechanism for providing compensation to the print mass 
media for the additional expenditure incurred in implementing 
this decree. 
  2. The Russian Federation Committee for the Press in 
conjunction with interested ministries, departments, and 
organizations shall draw up within one month proposals: 

  -  on the favorable taxation of the print mass media, as well 
as publications of children's, teaching, and other socially 
important literature; 
  -  on the system of state subsidies for the print mass media. 
  3. The Russian Federation Ministry of Communications in 
conjunction with interested organizations shall prepare within 
one month proposals to improve the system for delivering and 
disseminating the print mass media. 
  4. The Russian Federation State Committee for the Management 
of State Property and the Russian Federation Committee for the 
Press in conjunction with interested ministries, departments, 
and organizations shall submit within two months to the Russian 
Federation Government proposals on the procedure for privatizing 
printing enterprises, including those forming part of publishing 
and printing complexes, these proposals being linked in with the 
participation of collectives at mass media editorial offices and 
book publishers in their flotation and privatization. 
  [Signed] V. Chernomyrdin, chairman of the Russian Federation 
Government 
  [Dated] Moscow, 10 January 1994 

</TEXT>

