<F P=106> ["Own Information", ITAR-TASS report under the "Yesterday" </F>
rubric: "President Personally Upheld Journalists' Interests"] 
  [Text] Russian Federation President Boris Yeltsin has 
given orders that the State Kremlin Palace be made available for 
the traditional journalists' ball 15 January, at which the 
annual awards ceremony of the Union of Journalists of Russia 
will take place. 
  As has already been reported, the previous day the 
journalists were denied the opportunity to hold the ball in this 
building as it it an "official facility." It took a personal 
intervention by the head of state for the journalists' request 
to be granted. 

