<H3> <TI>   Party Leaders, Officials Preview Clinton's Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   LDPU Leader: Talks `Diplomatic Success' </H4>
<F P=102> LD1201121894 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 0848 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1201121894 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kiev -- Volodymyr Klymchuk, the chairman of the 
Liberal Democratic Party of Ukraine [LDPU], assesses a 
Ukrainian-Russian-American meeting in Moscow to be a Ukrainian 
diplomatic success. Talking with a UNIAN correspondent, he 
pointed out that future negotiations testified to the fact that 
Ukraine was recognized as a partner possessing equal rights. 
The fact that negotiations were being held, in Volodymyr 
Klymchuk's view, means that the United States and Russia agree 
to make concessions, and it is quite possible that a decision 
will be made that will be favorable for Ukraine. "Anyway, 
political trading is better than war," the LDPU chairman said. 

</TEXT>

