<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Party Leaders, Officials Preview Clinton's Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   MP Welcomes Kravchuk-Clinton Meeting </H4>
<F P=102> LD1201132194 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 0848 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1201132194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kiev -- Asked by a UNIAN correspondent on 11 January 
to comment on the expected meeting between the Ukrainian, 
Russian, and U.S. Presidents, Oles Shevchenko, the deputy 
chairman of the Ukrainian Republican Party and people's deputy 
of Ukraine said: "He who finds opportunities for talks and 
meetings in any situation is a wise politician." Shevchenko 
added that he welcomed Leonid Kravchuk's decision to meet 
William Clinton in Kiev and take part in negotiations in Moscow. 
"I hope that decisions taken by the Ukrainian Parliament -- and 
that on the ratification of the START I Treaty in particular -- 
will be complied with in possible agreements," he noted. 

</TEXT>

