<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk, Clinton Discuss Wide Range of Issues </TI></H3>
<H4>   Students Demonstrate During Clinton Visit </H4>
<F P=102> LD1301105194 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 0953 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1301105194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Kiev -- U.S. President Bill Clinton arrived in 
the Ukrainian capital on a visit lasting several hours on 12 
January. [passage omitted] During the negotiations between the 
U.S. and Ukrainian presidents, activists from the Popular 
Movement of Ukraine [Rukh] and the Union of Ukrainian Students 
were holding a demonstration with slogans in their hands. In 
particular, among them were the following: "Clinton, we warn 
you: first Crimea then Alaska," "disarmament threatens Europe," 
"No to the new world divide," "All rockets to Zhirinovskiy?," 
"Bill, would you disarm if you were in the same cage as the 
Russian bear?" 

</TEXT>

