<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Deputies Debate Validity of Nuclear Agreement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201140394 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 1207 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1201140394 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kiev, 12 Jan -- As Anatoliy Matviyenko, a member of 
the Supreme Council presidium told a UNIAR correspondent on 11 
January, Supreme Council Chairman Ivan Plyushch urgently 
interrupted his holiday to return to Kiev. He held a meeting 
with the participation of presidium members of the Ukrainian 
Supreme Council and the leadership of the secretariat. They 
decided to hold on 12 January a joint meeting of the Supreme 
Council standing commissions. 
  As Matviyenko noted, the urgent convening of the meeting is 
connected with the Kravchuk and Clinton meeting and in 
particular with the possibility of signing, on 14 January in 
Moscow, a document on issues of disarmament. Since, in the 
opinion of some deputies, the signing of such a document by 
Kravchuk is a direct violation of current legislation and 
Ukraine's Constitution and contradicts many points of the 
conditions to the ratification of the START Treaty of 18 
November, Ukraine's Supreme Council should draw up a single 
position on these issues. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

