<H3> <TI>   Agreement on Crime Prevention Initialed With Israel </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1201132894 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 1100 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS1201132894 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to information from the Center for Public 
Relations of the Ukrainian Ministry of Internal Affairs, today 
in the Ukrainian Ministry of Internal Affairs, the Ukrainian 
minister of internal affairs and Israeli minister of police, 
energy, and infrastructure initialed an agreement on cooperation 
in the area of crime prevention and law breaking between the two 
countries. A news conference for journalists was then held. 
Answering journalists' questions, Israeli Minister Moshe Shahal 
stated that Israeli police pay special attention to crime 
prevention, which is a task for the entire state, not just the 
police. The use of firearms by criminals, as well as drug 
smuggling were also discussed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

