<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Satisfied With Visit to PRC </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201181694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1615 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1201181694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [by ITAR-TASS correspondent Pavel Spirin] </F>
  [Text] Beijing January 12 TASS -- The Chinese Armed Forces 
will never act as an aggressor. But they will not tolerate any 
aggression against China either, Deputy Chairman of the Chinese 
Central Military Council, Zhang Zhen, said. 
  The statement was made at Zhen's [as received] meeting with 
visiting Kazakh Defence Minister Sagadat Nurmagambetov. Zhen 
said the Chinese Army is based on the concept of active defence 
and bears full responsibility for the preservation of the 
socialist system in China. 
  Nurmagambetov praised the achievements of economic reform in 
China. The XINHUA news agency quoted him as saying that "we 
should learn Chinese experience." 
  The minister expressed satisfaction with the results of his 
visit the aim of which he formulated before his departure to 
Beijing as follows: "The establishment of personal contacts 
with Chinese colleagues and development of friendly relations 
between the armies of the two countries." 

</TEXT>

