<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reaction to Russian Generals' Detention </TI></H3>
<H4>   Riga Reports on Apology </H4>
<F P=102> LD1201131594 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1200 GMT 12 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1201131594 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Latvian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Foreign Affairs Ministry Press Center of the 
Republic of Latvia reports that the Foreign Affairs Ministry has 
submitted a note to the Russian Federation embassy in Latvia. 
  In the note, the ministry apologizes for the incident of 10 
January, and explains that preliminary investigation has been 
made into the case and the person guilty of it was dismissed 
from office. As the above-mentioned incident happened on the 
very eve of the interstate talks, Latvia considers it as an 
attempt by certain circles in Latvia to hamper the progress of 
the talks and complicate interstate relations. 
  The note says that the Latvian Government will do everything 
possible to ward off such provocations in future, and stresses 
that in future all the issues related to the withdrawal of the 
Russian Army will also be tackled by way of talks. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

