<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Considerable Progress' Made on Skrunda Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201172594 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1600 GMT 12 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1201172594 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Latvian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Considerable progress has been made in two days of 
Latvian-Russian interstate talks on the issue of the definition 
of the status of the Skrunda radar station. This was reported 
today by the head of the Russian delegation, Sergey Zotov. 
  Zotov explained that disagreements in the opinions of the 
two 
delegations on draft agreements on the status of the Skrunda 
radar, and the period for which it will remain in Latvia, as 
well as on social security for the Russian military personnel 
are the only obstacles that hamper the signing of the joint 
agreement on the withdrawal of the Russian Army. 

</TEXT>

