<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Diplomatic Protocol Signed With Azerbaijan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201162794 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1500 GMT 12 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1201162794 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Latvian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ojars Kehris, Latvia's minister of economics, and 
Samad Sadykov, vice premier of Azerbaijan [title as received], 
today in Baku, signed an agreement on trade and economic 
cooperation between Latvia and Azerbaijan. 
  Moreover, Kehris and the Azerbaijani foreign minister, Gasan 
Gasanov, signed a protocol on the establishment of diplomatic 
relations between Latvia and Azerbaijan. 
  According to the agreement, Azerbaijan will supply Latvia 
with fuel and oil products. Latvia, for its part, will supply 
Azerbaijan with engines, wagons, as well as products of the 
instrument-making industry. 

</TEXT>

