<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Kehris Comments on Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201200094 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1801 GMT 12 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1201200094 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Latvian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Economics Minister Ojars Kehris reported on 
returning to Latvia that during a visit to Baku an official 
Latvian government delegation established diplomatic relations 
with Azerbaijan and concluded a trade and economic cooperation 
agreement. 
  The Latvian delegation met Azerbaijani President Geydar 
Aliyev and representatives of the government. 
  Due to the unstable political situation and the state of war 
in Azerbaijan, possibilities for cooperation are limited, but 
successful development cannot be ruled out in the future. 
  Latvia also plans to conclude similar agreements with 
Kazakhstan and Uzbekistan. 

</TEXT>

