<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Decision on Soviet Secret Documents </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301105394 Vilnius Radio Vilnius International Service in 
Lithuanian 2200 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1301105394 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius Radio Vilnius International Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Lithuanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Lithuanian Government declared at its closed 
meeting on Wednesday [12 January] as restricted all secret 
documents of the government institutions, the procuracy, courts, 
all structures of the Lithuanian Communist Party, offices, 
enterprises, and organizations during the period of Soviet 
occupation of Lithuania. 
  The government press representative also announced that it 
was decided at the same meeting to abolish unilaterally visas to 
the citizens of Japan, Switzerland, Liechtenstein, and Italy. 

</TEXT>

