<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Parliament Votes To Prohibit Gambling </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1201203094 Tallinn BNS in English 1638 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1201203094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vilnius, Jan 12, BNS - The Lithuanian parliament 
prohibited gambling and casinos Tuesday [11 January] by adopting 
several amendments to the law on enterprises. 
  The step earned sizable support from the rightist opposition 
but was sharply criticized by some members of the ruling 
majority. Kestutis Jaskelevicius, chairman of the parliament's 
Budget and Finance Committee, ironically remarked that the next 
step would be to impose a ban on short skirts. 
  A special commission of the Lithuanian Finance Ministry said 
the move would eliminate possibilities to root out illegal 
casinos by applying economic methods and to get additional 
budget receipts. 
  A similar view was expressed by Finance Minister Eduardas 
Vilkelis. 
  The parliament ignored the commission's arguments because 
"believers pray for such a decision." The law will come into 
effect if it is signed by the president. 
  The regulations of establishing casinos and gambling rules 
were approved by the Lithuanian government only a half year ago. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

