<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roads to Dushanbe Reportedly Blocked by Fighting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201170694 (Clandestine) Voice of Free Tajikistan in Tajik 
0900 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1201170694 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of Free Tajikistan </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Tajik </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The rumors about the blockade of the roads leading 
to the city of Dushanbe by Regarskiy and Gissarskiy fighting 
groups have been confirmed. 
  According to the report by Sharif Rrahmonpur, a KHORASAN 
news 
agency correspondent in Dushanbe city, the confrontation between 
the government and Safarali Kenjayev, the former parliament 
speaker, who is at the head of Regarskiy and Gissarskiy 
formations, is growing day by day. 
  The blockade of the roads leading to the capital and clashes 
between these formations and Kulyab fighters are evidence of 
that. 
  The correspondent reports that a clash took place between 
the 
fighting sides near the village of Almaasi of Gissarskiy Rayon 
on Monday. 
  According to available information, the fighters of 
Regarskiy 
and Gissarskiy demand the resignation of Abdulmajid Dostiyev 
[first deputy chairman of the Supreme Council], Yokubjon Salimov 
[internal affairs minister], and [Saydamir] Zukhurov [National 
Security Committee chairman], the representatives of Kulyab 
Oblast, and restoration of Safarali Kenjayev to his former post 
[Supreme Council chairman]. 

</TEXT>

