<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Border `Armed Provocations' Become More Frequent </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301001994 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1930 GMT 
12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1301001994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Slavyanka" program of the Russian Defense </F>
Ministry] 
  [Text] According to reports from Tajikistan, since the 
beginning of January armed provocations on certain sections of 
the Tajik-Afghan border have become much more frequent, first 
and foremost, in the assigned area of responsibility of the 
Moscow and Pyandzh detachments of the Russian border troops. 
Posts and outposts periodically come under unprovoked fire from 
Afghan territory. 
  In the last five days the border guards of the Pyandzh 
border 
detachment stopped three attempts of armed groups of mojahedin 
of the Tajik opposition to break through the border from 
Afghanistan. Fortunately, there have been no losses among the 
Russian servicemen. 

</TEXT>

