<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rakhmanov Calls On `Compatriots' To Return </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201190394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1806 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1201190394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Galina Gridnevadushanbe] </F>
  [Text] January 12 TASS -- An address by Tajik leader 
Emomali Rakhmonov to his compatriots outside Tajikistan was 
released here on Wednesday. The address says, in particular, 
that "we hope that you, our dear compatriots abroad, will take 
an active part in Tajikistan's future political and economic 
life. The Tajik leadership is ready to create all necessary 
conditions for you to return". The document notes that at 
present the republic was taking efforts to stabilize the 
internal situation, and every Tajik citizen should contribute to 
the flourishing of this ancient land. Fruitful negotiations 
with the republic's different political forces have been under 
way for several months already. Now it is necessary to discuss 
comprehensively Tajikistan's new constitution and put it to a 
nationwide popular vote. 

</TEXT>

