<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Deputies To Be Proposed 14 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301153494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1413 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1301153494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Speaker of the Federation Council Vladimir Shumeyko, 
elected to the post Thursday, has told the deputies that he 
intends to do his best for the Federation Council as the supreme 
body of state power. By Shumeyko's proposal, it was decided to 
make nominations for the post of the deputy speaker on Friday 
morning. 
  Before that he intends to hold consultations on candidates 
with different deputy factions. 
  In line with the earlier approved regulations, the speaker 
of 
the Federation Council will have three deputies. 
  Shumeyko said that all deputies, despite their posts, will 
have equal rights. 
  One member of Shumeyko's team has described as a convincing 
victory Shumeyko's election to the post of the speaker. No one 
can reproach Shumeyko for victory due to pressure groups. 
Ninety-eight votes were cast by convincing supporters of 
Vladimir Shumeyko, he said. 

</TEXT>

