<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy To Run for State Duma Speaker </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201180494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1753 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1201180494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Pavel Kuznetsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 12 TASS -- Russian nationalist leader 
Vladimir Zhirinovskiy who was said to be planning to become the 
chairman of the Foreign Affairs Commission of the State Duma is 
now running for the post of the speaker whom the lower chamber 
plans to elect Thursday. 
  He is among eight candidates to the post nominated by seven 
party factions and independent deputies. The Russia's Choice 
keeps its candidate in secret so far, Sergey Stankevich, head of 
the interim secretariat of the Duma, said on Wednesday after a 
meeting of faction leaders. 
  Other candidates are--Vladimir Medvedev from Independents, 
Ivan Rybkin from Agrarians, Sergey Glazyev from the Democratic 
Party, Alevtina Fedulova from the Women of Russia Bloc, Sergey 
Shakhray from the Party of Russian Unity and Accord, Vladimir 
Lukin from the Yabloko Bloc, and Mikhail Lapshin from Communists. 
  "Although the Russia's Choice has a candidate it does not 
name him," Stankevich said. 

</TEXT>

