Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Pavel Kuznetsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 12 TASS -- Twenty independent members 
of the State Duma (lower chamber of the new Russian legislature) 
have decided to join the centrist parliamentary faction of 
Sergey Shakhray's Party of Russian Unity and Accord (PRES). 
  All the volunteers represent interests of Russia's new 
financial and industrial sector, Aleksandr Kotenkov, acting 
executive committee's chairman of the PRES, told ITAR-TASS on 
