  [Text] Interfax reports that Leonid Grach, the Communist 
Party's candidate for the post of Crimean president, narrowly 
escaped an assassination attempt yesterday evening. The bullet, 
fired at the party's headquarters, slightly wounded the occupant 
of an armchair vacated by Leonid Grach 20 minutes earlier, when 
he left to take part in a radio debate. 

