<H3> <TI>   Central Electoral Commission Registers 2 More Parties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201140694 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 0848 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1201140694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kiev -- On 11 January, the Central Electoral 
Commission issued registration certificates to the 
Constitutional Democratic Party, the Party of the Organization 
of Ukrainian Nationalists in Ukraine, and the Peasant Democratic 
Party of Ukraine in connection with their intention to nominate 
candidates for participation in the elections of Ukrainian 
people's deputies on 27 March 1994. Thus, 23 political parties 
have been issued their Central Electoral Commission registration 
certificates by now. 

