<H3> <TI>   Parliament Budgets 650 Billion Rubles for Army </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1201131194 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 11 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM1201131194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Valeriy Kovalev report under the "Yesterday" rubric: </F>
"Belarusian Military Budget Only Sufficient To Feed Army"] 
  [Text] Minsk -- The Belarusian Supreme Soviet has adopted 
a law on the state budget for 1994. The republic's difficult 
economic and financial position has forced parliamentarians to 
cut military expenditure to a minimum. 
  The Republic of Belarus Ministry of Defense has been 
allocated a little over 650 billion rubles [R] from the state 
"purse," which constitutes roughly 4 percent of the budget's 
expenditure section. The lion's share of these funds will go to 
pay monetary allowances to servicemen, to pay for communal 
services, and to provide the Army with food and clothing. A 
total of R18 billion -- around 3.5 [figure as published] percent 
of the military budget -- is earmarked for the purchase of 
hardware and arms, and the spare parts for them. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

