<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reform Movement Splits at Annual Conference </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1201170394 Minsk VECHERNIY MINSK in Russian 10 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> WS1201170394 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk VECHERNIY MINSK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Valeriy Stepanov under the "Political Zodiac" </F>
rubric: "Split in the Movement"] 
  [Text] This last time around, the annual conference of the 
Movement for Democratic Reforms -- Democratic Belarus [MDBDR] 
was held behind closed doors. While discussing program goals 
and tasks, the conference split in two. A group of participants 
and MDBDR Cochairman Leonid Zlotnikov found their further 
participation in the conference, as well as in the MDBDR, 
impossible. 
  The discord was provoked both by ideological concerns and, 
according to those who left the conference room, a breach of the 
agreed-upon time limit. One MDBDR leader, Olga Abramova, who 
shares the ideas and approaches of the Civic Union in Russia, 
thinks that the Movement should learn from Volski [leader of the 
Civic Union in Russia], while Leonid Zlotnikov and his adherents 
are more inclined to follow the Gaydar line. It is possible, 
according to a BELAPAN correspondent, that the former members of 
the MDBDR will join the United Democratic Party of Belarus. 

</TEXT>

