<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Military Cooperation Agreement With Chechnya Prepared </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201132994 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1200 GMT 
12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1201132994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A draft cooperation agreement is being prepared 
between the military departments of the Russian Federation and 
the Chechen Republic. 
  Journalists have been told by Colonel Musa Mirzhoyev, a 
spokesman for the president of Chechnya at the headquarters of 
the Chechnya armed forces, that the draft agreement envisages 
preserving the single defense space. According to this 
document, the Russian side has to provide Chechnya's troops with 
weapons, not to use its army against the Chechen Republic, train 
Chechen military experts and provide assistance in the 
maintenance of military equipment. If necessary, the Chechen 
side is obliged to give the Russian forces the use of their 
airfields, to take part in joint military manoeuvers and 
exercises and not to join any bloc opposing the Russian 
Federation. 

</TEXT>

