<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   State of Emergency Extended for 6 Months </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201133994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1312 
GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1201133994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By TIA correspondent Negmat Ochilov for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Dushanbe, 12 Jan -- The Supreme Council Presidium of 
the Republic of Tajikistan has extended its decree of 6 January 
1993 "On the introduction of a state of emergency in Dushanbe, 
the town of Tursunzade and its rayon, Shakhrinavskiy, 
Gissarskiy, Leninskiy, and Varzobskiy rayons, as well as the 
town of Kofarnikhon and its rayon for six months, until 8 June 
1994." This measure was taken in order to stabilize the 
situation, establish the rule of law, and ensure the security of 
citizens, on the basis of Article 108 of the Constitution of 
Tajikistan. 

