<H3> <TI>   Georgian Delegation Member Comments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1201190494 Tbilisi First Program Television Network in 
Georgian 1700 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1201190494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi First Program Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Georgian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Batoni [Georgian polite form of address] Aleksandr 
Kavsadze, a member of the Georgian delegation at the Geneva 
negotiations, said today in a conversation with a TV 
correspondent that the first day of the negotiations could be 
assessed as constructive and businesslike. 
  As during the first round of talks, our delegation was led 
by 
Batoni Jaba Ioseliani. He presented our proposals concerning 
what questions had to discussed and the views of the Georgian 
delegation as to how these questions should be resolved. On the 
instructions of the head of state, attention was focused on the 
principal question of the return of refugees to their places of 
residence. 
  One of the main questions (?discussed) during the 
negotiations yesterday was the (?return) of refugees. We 
listened to specific proposals presented by the UN High 
Commission, and the Russian side also had specific proposals. 
So, there were serious talks yesterday regarding this question. 
  We listened to information presented by a group of experts. 
They agreed that, today, fundamental documents regarding these 
questions would be prepared and there would also be talks 
regarding individual programs relating to these individual 
questions. 

</TEXT>

