<H3> <TI>   New Wave Union Leader Criticizes Disarmament Pact </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1401090494 Lvov POST-POSTUP in Ukrainian 1600 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1401090494 </F>
<F P=104>  Lvov POST-POSTUP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The agreement that is to be signed in Moscow will 
definitely rescind Ukraine's nuclear status, stated Taras 
Stetskiv, one of the leaders of the New Wave union, in an 
interview with the Lvov Television Company Mist on 13 January. 
In exchange for ephemeral international aid, Ukraine will 
recklessly dispose of its nuclear weapons. Stetskiv spoke in 
favor of simultaneous disarmament of all nuclear states. The 
only promising news is that the agreement must be ratified by 
the Supreme Council, he added, and this is very unlikely to 
occur. 
  Stetskiv believes that the negative aspect of the 
Partnership 
for Peace initiative is that it contradicts the idea of the 
Baltic-Black Sea Commonwealth; one positive aspect is that it 
has been offered to Ukraine along with other Central Europe 
countries, but not Russia. This, in his opinion, gives a chance 
for Ukraine's integration with Europe without Russia. We should 
knock more decisively on Europe's door, concluded Stetskiv. 

</TEXT>

