<H3> <TI>   Oil, Gas Cooperation Agreements Signed With Israel </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301140694 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 0953 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1301140694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Kiev -- A joint news conference was held on 12 
January at Ukraine's Ministry of Internal Affairs between Andriy 
Vasylyshyn, Ukraine's minister of internal affairs, and Moshe 
Shahal, the Israeli minister of police and of energy and 
infrastructure. [passage omitted] 
  On the same day a protocol of intent was signed at the State 
Committee of Ukraine for Oil and Gas. Guidelines for 
development and the timescale for submitting specific proposals 
from the two sides were outlined. 
  A similar agreement, but only verbally, was reached at 
Ukraine's Ministry of Power Engineering and Electrification. 
Proposals were received on cooperation with the Ukrainian State 
Committee on Nuclear and Radiation Safety. 
  "This is the first attempt by Ukrainian and Israeli power 
engineers to establish relations between both countries' power 
engineers," said Amnon Ainav [name as received] scientific 
director of Israel's Ministry of Power Engineering, in an 
interview with a UNIAN correspondent. A meeting at the level of 
experts is planned for the end of March, where cooperation for 
using solar energy and other nontraditional forms of energy will 
be agreed. 

</TEXT>

