<H3> <TI>   `Sensational Document' Shows Aid to Abkhazia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301143794 Tbilisi IBERIA in Georgian 1115 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1301143794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi IBERIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Georgian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tbilisi, 13 Jan -- An Iberia correspondent learned 
that the all-Georgia Merab Kostava Society has obtained a 
sensational document which proves that on 14 April 1992 -- that 
is three months before the war broke out in Abkhazia -- Russia's 
President Boris Yeltsin gave an order to the heads of 
Krasnodarskiy and Stavropolskiy kray administrations to speed up 
establishing direct economic links with Abkhazia, avoiding 
Georgia. 

</TEXT>

