<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fighting Continues on Karabakh Front 13 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1301140494 Yerevan ARMENPRES International Service in 
Armenian 1243 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1301140494 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan ARMENPRES International Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Armenian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, 13 Jan (ARMENPRES)--The battles resumed 
this morning in the southeastern sector of the Karabakh battle 
front on the border of Martuninskiy Rayon. The Nagorno-Karabakh 
Republic [NKR] Defense Army press service reported that the 
Karabakh fighters were still resisting the enemy's pressure as 
of 1200. Particularly fierce battles were waged in this sector 
of the front yesterday. The Karabakh troops managed to halt all 
the attacks of the enemy and threw him back to his former 
positions. 
  The Azerbaijani Army's attempts to breach Karabakh's 
defensive lines to the north and northeast of the NKR also 
failed. 
  The enemy lost nearly 50 soldiers and two tanks during the 
battles during the past day. Two fighters were killed and seven 
injured on the Karabakh side. 

</TEXT>

