<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Iranian President Sends Message to Ter-Petrosyan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1401101294 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0430 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1401101294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Armenian president has stressed the importance 
of his country's relations with the Islamic Republic of Iran and 
has called for the broadening of bilateral relations and 
cooperation. 
  According to IRNA, a verbal message from President Hashemi- 
Rafsanjani was conveyed by the director general of the CIS desk 
at our Foreign Ministry during his meeting with Armenian 
President Levon Ter-Petrosyan yesterday. 
  In the course of this meeting, regional developments and the 
Islamic Republic of Iran's efforts for the establishment of 
peace in the Nagorno-Karabakh region were assessed. The 
director general of the CIS desk at our Foreign Ministry also 
met the Armenian vice president and the foreign minister and 
delivered a written message from Dr. Velayati to the latter. 
  During the meeting, the Armenian foreign minister stressed 
that the Islamic Republic of Iran can play an important role in 
resolving the Nagorno-Karabakh problem. He called for our 
country's cooperation in containing this crisis. 

</TEXT>

