<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Armenians Shell Southwestern Border Districts </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1301181294 Baku AZERTAC in English 1257 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1301181294 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku AZERTAC </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baku, January 13 (AZERTAC]--The Armenian armed 
forces suffering defeat caused by the Azeri national army, 
decided to revenge itself on civilian population of Azerbaijan. 
The districts of Kazakhskiy, Kedabekskiy and Tauzskiy, which 
border on Armenia in the south-west, were subject to heavy 
shelling of the Armenian artillery yesterday. There are victims 
and heavy destruction. 
  The Defence Ministry says yesterday's fight did not change 
the situation at the front. The Armenian armed forces attempts 
to attack the village of Hakop-Kamari from Terter, Agdam and 
Beylagan directions were stopped by the Azeri national army. 
The enemy suffered heavy casualties. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

