<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Attacks Repelled; Losses Inflicted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301145794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1406 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1301145794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By AZERTAC for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Baku January 13 TASS -- Azerbaijan succeeded to 
repell two Armenian attacks and said that the enemy had 
sustained major losses. 
  The Republican Defence Ministry said on Thursday that an 
Armenian tank and an armoured personnel carrier were destroyed 
in fighting in Fizuli region and another tank, a mortar and 
nearly one hundred mines were seized from retreating Armenians. 
  A major Armenian unit got onto a mine field while 
approaching 
the city of Agdam. The Azerbaijani troops delivered flank 
strikes on Armenians who fled the battle scene leaving major 
losses behind them, according to the source. 
  The ministry also said that casualties and damage were 
reported in Azeri border settlements in the north-west of the 
country in two days of intensive Armenian shelling from 
long-range artillery. 

</TEXT>

