<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gasanov Rejects Armenian Claims on Azeri Losses </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301220794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1812 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1301220794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Azerbaijan's Foreign Minister, Gasan Gasanov, 
declared in his interview with Interfax that assertions by 
Armenian sources about great losses by the Azerbaijani army 
during hostilities in Nagorno-Karabakh are nothing more than 
lies. 
  He pointed out that "this is the product of work of the 
Armenian propaganda machine." The Armenian party, the minister 
said, strives to suppress the spirit of the Azerbaijani army 
while simultaneously trying to raise the spirit of its own army. 
  Gasanov again accused the Armenian party of attempts to 
solve 
the Karabakh conflict by coercive methods. 

</TEXT>

