<H3> <TI>   Cosmonauts Land Safely After Collision With Space Station </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1401105194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1007 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1401105194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Veronika Romanenkova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 14 TASS -- The Soyuz TM-17 spaceship 
with cosmonauts Vasiliy Tsibliyev and Aleksandr Serebrov aboard 
safely landed, as planned, on Friday at 11 hr 18 min 20 sec, 
Moscow time, ITAR-TASS learnt at the press centre of the Russian 
Space-Military Forces. 
  The spaceship safely landed (despite a collision with the 
Mir 
space station reported by the Ostankino radio station) 215 
kilometers west of the city of Karaganda, Kazakhstan. 
  The crew is planned to be brought to Moscow later in the 
day. 

</TEXT>

