<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Aide Advocates Change in Taxation Targets </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1301152994 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 13 Jan 94 
First Edition p 3 </F>

<F P=103> PM1301152994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Ground Rent Instead of Profits Tax?"] </F>
  [Text] Petr Filippov, head of the presidential 
administration's analytical center for socioeconomic policy, 
supports the idea of fundamental reform of the tax system. 
  The idea was voiced by participants in an economic 
conference 
of scientific and business circles. 
  "I am in favor of switching to taxation of natural resources 
and using ground rent instead of stifling taxes on profits and 
wages," P. Filippov said. However, some other proposals made 
during the conference "create a complex impression," he said. 
In particular, in P. Filippov's opinion, the proposal from one 
of the conference organizers, the economist Sergey Glazyev, for 
a "compulsory freeze on amortization payments" would ruin 
enterprises. 
  The head of the presidential administration's analytical 
center is also worried by the "talk about enforced vertical 
integration of industry." "We had this with ministries and 
departments. If we want to create viable financial and 
industrial complexes, they must develop from the mutual 
interests of the participants and not according to the will of 
state officials," he said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

