<H3> <TI>   Faction Signals Willingness for NATO Plan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301210894 Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network in Estonian 1400 
GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1301210894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Estonian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The parliament foreign commission has proposed to 
the government to signal readiness for participation in the 
Partnership for Peace program and to sign a basic document to 
this end. The parliament foreign commission also recommends 
that the government should present to NATO Estonian proposals to 
draw up an Estonian-NATO partnership program while also 
consulting relevant parliament commissions. 
  The parliament foreign commission took this decision after 
it 
had familiarized itself with the documents of the NATO heads of 
state and government leaders' conference. As is known the 
meeting took place in Brussels on 10 and 11 January. 

</TEXT>

