<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Envoy-Designate Supports NATO Plan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1301201494 Tallinn ETA NEWS RELEASE in English 1743 GMT 13 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS1301201494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn ETA NEWS RELEASE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Estonia's former Foreign Minister Trivimi Velliste 
who will this summer become the country's ambassador to the 
United Nations said NATO programme "Partnership for Peace" was 
very favourable to Estonia as there were no alternatives. 
  "If the programme will be developed in a way that Estonia 
has 
enough time to join in and this way develop its own political 
and national defence structures, practical cooperation with NATO 
and bringing Estonia's national defence in line with NATO 
standards will become possible in near future," Velliste said. 

</TEXT>

