<H3> <TI>   Commission Urges Plan Acceptance </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1301200394 Tallinn ETA NEWS RELEASE in English 1606 GMT 13 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS1301200394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn ETA NEWS RELEASE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The foreign relations commission of Estonian 
parliament on Thursday presented the government a package of 
proposals on relations with NATO after looking through the 
documents of the Brussels meeting of the heads of government and 
state of NATO countries that was held on January 10-11. 
  The commission proposed to express willingness to 
participate 
in "Partnership for Peace" programme, to sign the initial 
documents, to present Estonian partnership proposals to NATO and 
put partnership programme into force by diplomatic procedures, 
the package signed by chairman of the commission, Vello 
Saatpalu, said. 

