<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Presented Blueprint for European Union </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1401075494 Tallinn BNS in English 1630 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1401075494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tallinn, Jan 13, BNS -- A governmental working 
group set up to prepare blueprints for Estonia's joining the 
European Union presented at today's Cabinet meeting a four-page 
program of action, Ivar Raig, the chairman of the group, told 
BNS. 
  The first part of the two-part program includes security, 
socioeconomic and legal issues that need to be coordinated; the 
second part deals with the methods and the mechanism of 
unification, Raig said. 
  "Estonia can realistically expect to join the European Union 
before the other former socialist countries," Raig claimed. The 
country's main goal is not to lag behind Ukraine, Slovenia and 
the Czech Republic that already have asked to be admitted to the 
union, he added. 
  The working group consists of a score of politicians and 
economics experts. Last week it appointed Priit Kolbre, the head 
of the Foreign Ministry's foreign economic policy department, as 
its secretary, Raig told BNS. 

</TEXT>

