<H3> <TI>   Federation Council Elects 2 Deputy Chairmen </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1401113894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1104 
GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1401113894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Lyudmila Aleksandrova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 14 January -- Two deputy chairmen of the 
upper chamber of parliament were elected today at a session of 
the Federation Council of the Russian Federal Assembly. They 
were Ramazan Abdulatipov, first deputy minister for 
nationalities affairs and regional policy, and Valeryan 
Viktorov, chairman of the Chuvash republic Council of Ministers. 
  A third deputy speaker was not elected because neither of 
the 
two nominees for this post -- Petr Romanov, general director of 
the "Yenisey" association, and Aleksandr Kovalev, head of the 
administration of Voronezh Oblast -- succeeded in acquiring the 
required majority of votes. As proposed by Federation Council 
Chairman Viktor Shumeyko, the elections for the third deputy 
were held over until the next meeting of the chamber. 
  The Federation Council is now debating the question of 
forming parliamentary committees. Work is proceeding in a calm 
and businesslike manner. 

</TEXT>

