<F P=102>  LD1301174194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1630 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1301174194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Ivan Novikov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 13 TASS -- Sergey Shakhray, the 
leader of the Party of Russian Unity and Accord who had long 
before elections said he would run for the speaker of the state 
Duma, refused to join the race on Thursday [13 January]. 
  He told lawmakers that he is quitting the race in favour of 
Vladimir Medvedev nominated by independent deputies. 
  "An independent candidate should be preferred in order not 
push the Duma into a deadend", Shakhray said. 

</TEXT>

