<H3> <TI>   Rybkin Elected Chairman </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1401114494 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1100 GMT 
14 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1401114494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Tellers Commission has just taken the rostrum 
and announced the respective votes. There were two candidates, 
I'd like to remind you -- Yuriy Petrovich Vlasov and Ivan 
Petrovich Rybkin -- and the vote went the following way: for 
Vlasov -- 23 deputies for and 311 against; for Rybkin -- 223 for 
and 101 against. So Ivan Petrovich Rybkin, representing the 
Agrarian Party, is elected chairman of the State Duma with one 
vote over the minimum. He needed 222 votes and got 223, so he 
has been elected. 
  But there is some discussion at the moment about one ballot 
being disputed, but it's difficult to say while this discussion 
is going on. So far, however, the news is that Rybkin, Ivan 
Petrovich, representative of the Agrarian Party, has been 
elected chairman of the State Duma. Thank you. 

</TEXT>

