<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   State Duma Defines Speaker's Powers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301202194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1812 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1301202194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The State Duma, the lower house of Russia's new 
parliament, has approved interim house rules on the powers of 
its Speaker. 
  The Speaker is responsible for house proceedings and routine 
preparation of questions for debate and for representing the 
Duma in relations with the President, federal and regional 
bodies, as well as with parliaments of other countries and 
inter-parliamentary groups. 
  He also represents the House in any conciliatory procedure 
envisaged by the country's constitution. 
  The House rejected a proposal from Kiril Ignatyev of the 
Russia's Choice faction calling to delete a clause on the 
Speaker's function of preparing questions for debate. 
  The Duma has also reached agreement on how to elect Speaker 
of the House. The deputies rejected the option of a secret 
ballot, settling for the Council of Factions' proposal for two 
rounds of voting to be held instead. 
  The names of two candidates who enlist more support than 
others in a straw vote will next be put forward for a secret 
ballot. 
  The Duma has now begun nominating candidates for the post. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

