<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Lawmaker Punches Zhirinovskiy at Lunch </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1401141994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1328 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1401141994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Ivan Novikov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 14 TASS -- Russian Nationalist Leader 
Vladimir Zhirinovskiy quarelled with lawmaker Mark Goryachev in 
the dining room during the lunch break in the Duma session on 
Friday and received a blow in the face, eye witnesses told TASS. 
  They said the quarrel emerged when one of the two Duma 
members wanted to jump the line for food, but could not say 
exactly whether it was Zhirinovskiy or Goryachev. 
  Anyway Goryachev, a prominent businessmen from St. 
Petersurg, 
hit Zhirinovskiy in the face leaving a bleeding scratch on it. 
  Police were called in and doctors rendered first aid to 
Zhirinovskiy. 
  The Russian Nationalist leader promised that Goryachev will 
be the first to get jailed in the notorious Lefortovo Prison, 
which used to belong to the KGB. Zhirinovskiy, evidently meant 
this would happen when he becomes the Russian president of which 
he is dreaming. 
  However, Goryachev is not the first man to receive such a 
threat from Zhirinovskiy. Right after the Decemeber 12 
elections Zhirinovskiy promised the same fate to Gennadiy 
khazanov, a famous comic who often mocks him. Khazanov 
responded by appearing in a show dressed as a convict with the 
number "001" sign on his shirt. 
  This is not the first case that Zhirinovskiy got beaten up. 
Before December elections bodyguards of popular singer Sofi 
Rotaru beat him up at a concert. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

