<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   State Duma Deputies Establish `Union of December 12' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301194494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1413 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1301194494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Up to 23 deputies of the State Duma are to set up a 
group named the Union of December 12, the Economic Freedom 
Party's Secretary-General Irina Khakamada told Interfax. 
Khakamada was elected this group's co-chairperson on Thursday. 
  The other co-chairpersons are member of the Moscow 
government 
Aleksandr Braginskiy and an entrepreneur from Nizhniy Novgorod 
Yevgeniy Bushmin. 
  To quote Khakamada, the Union of December 12 consists of 
lawyers, entrepreneurs and economists. It will not join any of 
the political factions. 
  She expressed hope that during the next three weeks the 
group 
will have 35 members which is sufficient for being registered. 

</TEXT>

