<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Meets Polish Counterpart in Grodno </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1401013694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1712 
GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1401013694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By BELINFORM correspondent for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Grodno, 13 Jan--An official meeting between 
Belarusian Defense Minister Pavel Kozlovskiy and Polish Defense 
Minister Reserve Vice Admiral Piotr Kolodziejczyk took place 
here today. This is the first meeting attended by Kolodziejczyk, 
who was appointed recently to the post of head of Poland's 
military department. 
  On the agenda were consultations on matters of military 
organizational development and cooperation in the area of 
defense between the two states and also on agreeing upon the 
forms of interaction between the military ministries in the 
realization of commitments entered into by the sides during the 
signing of the corresponding bilateral agreements in April 1993. 
  Questions concerning the preservation of peace and security 
in Europe were also touched upon. 

</TEXT>

