<F P=102>  WS1301195294 Tallinn BNS in English 1759 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1301195294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Riga, Jan 13, BNS -- Latvian Defense Minister 
Valdis Pavlovskis will recommend his government to accept NATO's 
invitation to join the Partnership for Peace program, the 
minister told BNS Thursday. 
  The final resolution rests with the Cabinet after it has 
received an official invitation from the alliance. 
  The Baltic presidents in their Jan. 11 statement already 
voiced their wish to participate in the cooperation plan, which 
NATO offers to the East European countries and the Baltic states 
as an avenue to eventual NATO membership. 
  Latvia has not decided yet how it will participate in the 
program. The establishment of the Baltic Peacekeeping Battalion 
is the first task now, said Pavlovskis. 

