<F P=101> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Liberal Democratic Party Withdraws From Coalition </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1401115394 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 0811 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1401115394 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Kharkov, 14 Jan -- The interpartite electoral 
association Spravedlyvist [Justice], uniting the Democratic 
Party, Republican Party, ChDPU [Christian Democratic Party] and 
Social Democratic Party in the general elections, has nominated 
its candidates for people's deputies. [passage omitted] 
  The Liberal Democratic Party of Ukraine [LDPU] has announced 
its secession from Spravedlyvist. Explaining this decision, 
party Chairwoman Yevheniya Novikova said that certain changes to 
the association's pre-election platform were introduced without 
consulting the LDPU. In particular, the provision on the 
possibility of a federal structure of Ukraine in the future was 
struck out. 

</TEXT>

