<H3> <TI>   Daily Questions Purity of NATO Membership Request </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1301125694 Tallinn BNS in English 1905 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1301125694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vilnius, Jan 12, BNS - Lithuanian President 
Algirdas Brazauskas pursued only one aim by asking for NATO 
membership -- he wanted to take away a trump card from the 
rightist opposition, which sharply criticized the administration 
for delaying an official request, the LIETUVOS RYTAS newspaper 
said in its editorial Wednesday [12 January]. 
  The newspaper said key issues in foreign policy are used 
only 
as a "tool for internal struggle" and a lacks a clear attitude 
toward this or that problem. 
  LIETUVOS RYTAS noted, however, that the international 
community heard Lithuania's name once again after a considerable 
break. "A majority of politicians consider the step premature, 
but they realized that Lithuania's aspiration is sincere -- to 
be safe on a dangerous crossing in Eastern Europe." 

</TEXT>

