<H3> <TI>   Further on Comments at News Conference </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1401032994 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 0200 
GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1401032994 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Urdu </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Sardar Asif Ahmad Ali has 
reaffirmed Pakistan's principled stand that the Kashmir issue 
should be resolved on the basis of the UN resolutions, and India 
should end its brutalities in occupied Kashmir. Addressing a 
joint news conference with his Kazakh counterpart in Almaty, he 
said both India and Pakistan are committed within the framework 
of the UN resolutions and the Simla Agreement to settle the 
Kashmir issue peacefully. He said Kashmiris have been subjected 
to the worst kind of genocide in the occupied territory by 
Indian forces, and India has also blocked all access to the 
Kashmir valley to the outside world, including humanitarian 
organizations. 
  Explaining Pakistan's peaceful nuclear program, the foreign 
minister said Pakistan has made a political decision not to make 
nuclear weapons. 

</TEXT>

