<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opposition Stops Refugees From Returning Home </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1401001794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1959 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1401001794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to Tajikistan's Foreign Ministry, the 
armed Tajik opposition is preventing Tajik refugees from 
returning home from Afghanistan. 
  A Foreign Ministry source told Interfax on Thursday [13 
January] that refugees were held up by opposition detachments 
based in Afghanistan's Konduz Province. 
  The source said the last meeting between Tajik and Afghan 
officials to discuss the refugees' repatriation took place near 
the Afghan town of Shir Khan on Wednesday. 
  Representatives of the Konduz governor once again assured 
the 
Tajik side that they would take urgent measures to unblock the 
road between the town of Konduz and the Shir Khan port to enable 
the refugees to return. 

</TEXT>

