<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Talbott Briefs Press on Yeltsin-Clinton 13 Jan Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1401092694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0727 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1401092694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Bogahev] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 14 TASS -- Strobe Talbott, assistant 
secretary of state of the United States, held a briefing at the 
American press centre in Hotel "Slavyanskaya" here in the early 
hours of January 14. He said that President Boris Yeltsin and 
President Bill Clinton had a meeting at Ogaryovo on January 13. 
  The two presidents discussed, in particular, some economic 
problems of mutual concern, questions linked with the 
"Partnership for Peace" programme, which was recently approved 
by the NATO leaders in Brussels, relations between the executive 
and legislative branches of government in both countries, the 
role of the military in the political lives of countries, 
proposals to promote cooperation between the military 
establishments of Russia and the United States. The sides also 
touched on problems of coordinating the policies of the United 
States and Russia in the Middle East, on the situation in former 
Yugoslavia. 
  President Yeltsin presented to Bill Clinton a porcelain 
statuette of the U.S. President. 

</TEXT>

