<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poltoranin Warns Clinton Against Meeting With Zhirinovskiy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301194194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1812 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1301194194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mikhail Poltoranin, a Duma member from the 
"Russia's Choice" bloc, believes that U.S. President Bill 
Clinton should not meet with Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, the leader 
of the Liberal Democratic Party. He told journalists on 
Thursday that instead of distinguishing between the notion of 
"Zhirinovskiy himself" and the "phenomenon of Zhirinovskiy," 
they had been giving too much publicity to him. 
  The phenomenon of Zhirinovskiy means discontent with 
official 
policy in Russia today. Zhirinovskiy is disgusting to many 
people, Poltoranin said, but they seem to have chosen the lesser 
of the two evils. And Clinton has been right to say that by 
voting for Zhirinovskiy citizens protested against the policy of 
the authorities. "The balloting showed that people had gotten 
tired of the helpless government, rampant bureaucracy, crime, 
etc. Official policy must be more effective," Poltoranin said. 

</TEXT>

