<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reaction to Clinton Visit Mixed </TI></H3>
<H4>   Communist's Zyuganov Comments </H4>
<F P=102> LD1301160194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1343 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1301160194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Pavel Kuznetsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 13 TASS -- Gennadiy Zyuganov, the 
leader of the Russian Communist Party, said the visit of the 
U.S. President "is exclusively important and timely as our 
political situation has changed and it is necessary (for Bill 
Clinton) to get acquainted with it". 
  Zyuganov told a press conference on Thursday that security 
issues should be in the focus of Russian-U.S. talks. 
  "The system of security in Russia is completely disorganised 
and the issue should be discussed in detail during the visit 
before the situation goes out of control completely", he said. 
  Speaking on Duma affairs, Zyuganov said that his party had 
already blocked with the Agrarian party and the Democratic 
Russia. 
  "Doors for others remain open", he stressed and added that 
communists are ready to unite with those factions which share 
three of their basic principles: peace in the country, 
well-being in every family and not only in elite families, the 
understanding that the current situation leads to chaos and 
upheavals. 
  Communists will focus on three tasks in the Duma and the 
major one is to change the course of reforms. The other two 
include the restoration of the state management in the country 
and moral improvement in society. 

</TEXT>

