<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reaction to Clinton Visit Mixed </TI></H3>
<H4>   Zhirinovskiy on `Pointless' Visit </H4>
<F P=102> LD1301155094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1413 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1301155094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Chairman of the Liberal Democratic Party Vladimir 
Zhirinovskiy believes that Bill Clinton's visit to Moscow is 
"pointless". 
  Zhirinovskiy told journalists that the U.S. president had 
arrived in Russia "to support the government whose policies were 
not backed by the people during the elections on December 12." 
  The day will come when America will appeal to Russia for 
help, he said. 

</TEXT>

