<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Joint Statements Issued, Declaration Signed </TI></H3>
<H4>   `Text' of Statement on Middle East </H4>
<F P=102> LD1401121294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1158 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1401121294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow January 14 TASS -- Follows the text of the 
Russian-US statement on the Middle East: 
  The Russian Federation and the United States of America, 
recognizing their special responsibility as cosponsors of the 
Middle East peace process, reiterate their firm commitment to 
achieving the goal of a comprehensive, just and lasting peace in 
the Middle East, based on resolutions 242 and 338 of the 
Security Council. 
  In moving towards this goal, Russia and the United States, 
building on the progress to date in the peace progress, are 
determined to support the efforts of the parties to implement 
the Palestinian-Israeli declaration of principles. 
Implementation of the declaration of principles is critical to 
changing the relationship between the israelis and the 
Palestinians. 
  Russia and the United States welcome progress achieved on 
the 
Jordanian-Israeli track of the peace process, and underscore 
their determination to help the parties make progress on the 
Syrian and Lebanese tracks as well. Both sides hope that in 
their quest for peace all participants in negotiations will 
display a high sense of responsibility, necessary flexibility 
and political farsightedness. 

</TEXT>

