<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1301103194 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 0400 
GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS1301103194 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In the course of the meeting between Russian 
President Boris Yeltsin and Belarusian Supreme Soviet Chairman 
Stanislav Shushkevich in Moscow on 12 January, both sides 
conducted an in-depth analysis of the state of bilateral 
relations, placing emphasis on economic cooperation. The sides 
came to the conclusion that a new Belarusian-Russian treaty on 
friendship and cooperation is necessary, corresponding to these 
states' aspiration to build democracies with socially-oriented 
market economies and the special status of economic, political, 
and human relations that have developed between the two 
countries in the course of history. The sides exchanged 
opinions with regard to the upcoming visit of U.S. President 
Bill Clinton to Moscow and Minsk. It was pointed out that in 
the process of building economic relations with the United 
States it is necessary to proceed from programs of assistance to 
programs of promoting trade and investment, being primary 
prerequisites for the development and integration of CIS 
economies in the world economy. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

