<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shuskevich Ends Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201195994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1922 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1201195994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow January 12 TASS -- Belarusian parliamentary 
speaker Stanislav Shushkevich left Moscow for Minsk on Wednesday 
upon completion of his one-day visit to Russia. 
  On Wednesday, Shushkevich had talks with Russian President 
Boris Yeltsin. Upon completion of the talks a joint communique 
was signed in which the sides expressed their common opinion 
that it is necessary to work out a new interstate 
Russo-Belarusian treaty on friendship and cooperation meeting 
the aspirations of both countries aimed at building democratic 
states with a socially-oriented market economy. 
  Yeltsin and Shushkevich exchanged opinions in connection 
with 
the expected visit by the U.S. President Bill Clinton to Moscow 
and Minsk. 

</TEXT>

