<H3> <TI>   Government Approves Draft Accord With Latvia on Travel </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301092094 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0800 GMT 
13 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1301092094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] ITAR-TASS reports that the Russian Government has 
approved a draft agreement with the Latvian Government on 
reciprocal visits by citizens. The document regulates the 
procedure for entry, exit, transit, and for the citizens of one 
state staying on the territory of the other using visas and 
documents recognized by both states as valid for foreign trips. 
  The head of the Russian delegation at the talks with Latvia, 
which, as is known, began in Riga on Tuesday, is instructed to 
sign the agreement on behalf of the Russian Government. 

</TEXT>

