<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shumeyko: `No Question' of Handing Over Kurils </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301152894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1413 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1301152894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The speaker of the Russian Federation Council 
Vladimir Shumeyko has said that he backs Prime Minister Viktor 
Chernomyrdin in terms of the disputed Northern Territories. He 
believes that the islands of Kunashir, Iturup, Shikotan and 
Habomai, claimed by Japan, "belong to Russia and there is no 
question of handing them over now." 
  Shumeyko was giving his first news conference as Speaker of 
the Upper House of the Russian Federal Assembly. 
  Shumeyko said that the prime minister's view was shared by 
the other Cabinet members. 
  At the same time Shumeyko admitted that this view was 
different somewhat from the official one. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

