<H3> <TI>   Meeting on Japanese Peace Treaty To Occur in Feb </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301175994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1613 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1301175994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Boris Krivoshey] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 13 TASS -- The joint working group 
for concluding a peace agreement between Russia and Japan, 
within the framework of which talks are being conducted over the 
disputed Kuril Islands, is expected to meet in the second half 
of February, a high-ranking official of the Russian Foreign 
Ministry told TASS on Thursday. 
  He denied the reports by the foreign mass media alleging 
that 
Russia had applied to Japan with a request to postpone 
indefinitely the meeting of the Russo-Japanese working group 
earlier scheduled for late January. At present, the Russian 
diplomat noted, officials of the Russian and Japanese foreign 
ministries are agreeing upon the concrete date of the meeting. 

</TEXT>

