<H3> <TI>   Submarines To Be Sold to North Korea as Scrap </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301192794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1748 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1301192794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Mikhail Shevtsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 13 TASS -- There is no secrecy about 
the transaction for the sale of Russian submarines with 
completed service life to North Korea. Indeed, such a contract 
was signed in full compliance with the existing rules and agreed 
with the Russian State Committee for Property. 
  A Japan firm will be engaged in dismantling Russian 
submarines, and they will be delivered to the buyer in a 
condition fit only for metal scrap, informed sources from the 
Russian Navy told ITAR-TASS today. 
  Thus, there are no grounds for the allegations that Russian 
submarines after necessary repairs can be put into service by 
subdivisions of the North Korean Navy. 

</TEXT>

