<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy Views Crimea Presidential Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301145594 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 0836 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1301145594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 12 Jan (UNIAR) -- Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, 
Russian Federation State Duma deputy and leader of the Liberal 
Democratic Party of Russia has made public a statement 
expressing support for Sergey Shuvaynykov, leader of the Russian 
Party of the Crimea, in the presidential elections of the 
Republic of Crimea. Incidentally, the Crimean regional branch 
of the Liberal Democratic Party of Russia, which has not been 
registered in Ukraine according to the established procedure, 
belongs to the Russian Party of Crimea as an associate member. 
Mr. Zhirinovksiy also expresses support for the Russian Party 
of Crimea during the elections to the Crimean Supreme Council, 
which will be held on 27 March 1994. 

</TEXT>

