<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry To Create Group To Support NATO Plan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1301195194 Tallinn BNS in English 1759 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1301195194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Riga, Jan 13, BNS -- The Latvian Foreign Ministry 
plans to set up a working party to support Latvia's 
participation in NATO's Partnership for Peace program. 
  The ministry will invite representatives of the Cabinet and 
officials of the Foreign Ministry and the Defense Ministry to 
join the group, which has not got a list of concrete members yet. 
  The group's foundation may be confirmed in the next Cabinet 
meeting, spokespeople said. 
  As reported, the Baltic presidents endorsed NATO's 
initiative 
in their Jan. 11 statement. The program offers the East European 
countries and the Baltic states a chance to cooperate with the 
alliance with a view to eventual membership. 

</TEXT>

