<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Assures Clinton on Reforms </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1401091194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0842 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1401091194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 14 TASS -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin reaffirmed his US counterpart Bill Clinton that Russian 
economic reforms are irreversible and said more attention will 
be paid to the social needs of the people. 
  Yeltsin "affirmed the irreversibility of Russia's transition 
to a market economy and his intention to further promote reforms 
and to address social needs associated with this transition", 
according to the Moscow declaration signed by the two Presidents 
on Friday. 
  "Clinton stressed his strong support for Russian reform and 
suggested that social issues could be a new and promising area 
for cooperation", the document said. 

</TEXT>

