<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev on Foreign Policy Issues Regarding CIS, Baltics </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801095494 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0900 GMT 
18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1801095494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Defending the rights and interests of Russian 
Federation citizens in the near abroad is one of Russia's main 
foreign policy tasks, Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev declared 
today at a conference on issues of foreign policy regarding the 
CIS and Baltic countries. Andrey Kozyrev singled out a number 
of foreign policy trends in this region: strengthening economic 
positions, enhancing the effectiveness of actions taken, and 
creating new mechanisms for cooperation. 
  Speaking about problems relating to how the CIS economic 
union functions, the foreign ministry head commented that Russia 
should try to avoid hasty decisions, in particular where 
creating single currencies is concerned. At the same time, he 
gave a positive evaluation of the recent agreement between 
Russian and Belarus on the forthcoming unification of currency 
systems, describing this as a good example of a well-considered 
agreement, INTERFAX reports. 

</TEXT>

