<H3> <TI>   Aide Says Kazakh Battalion To Fulfill Tajikistan Mission </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1401133594 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 14 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM1401133594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Anatoliy Ladin report under "Yesterday" rubric: </F>
"Kazakhstan Will Fulfill Its Peacemaking Mission to the End"] 
  [Text] As Tulegen Zhukeyev, state counselor of the 
Republic of Kazakhstan, told journalists, the Kazakh battalion 
presently stationed in Khorog, the administrative center of the 
Gorno-Badakhshan Autonomous Oblast, which is working with 
Russian border guards to protect the Tajik-Afghan border, will 
not be withdrawn from the Repulbic of Tajikistan. 
  All that is happening is that servicemen whose contracts 
have 
expired are being replaced. Zhukeyev stressed that Kazakhstan 
is consistently fulfilling all the documents signed by it 
regarding participation in the peacemaking mission in Tajikistan. 

</TEXT>

