<H3> <TI>   Azerbaijan Proposes Immediate Cease-Fire at Tbilisi Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1601214194 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 2100 GMT 
16 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1601214194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] During the meeting in Tbilisi between Mamedov and 
Sarkisyan, the ministers of defense of Azerbaijan and Armenia, 
the Azerbaijani side proposed an immediate cease-fire right 
along the Armenian-Azerbaijani frontline and the opening of a 
political dialogue by both sides including at presidential 
level. Interfax reported that the Armenian side was not 
prepared to take these decisions. The sides agreed to continue 
consultations between the heads of military departments. 

</TEXT>

